# Git main trunk & merge hygiene (CANON)

Canonical mall: [`docs/MERGE-IMPACT-RAPPORT.md`](../../docs/MERGE-IMPACT-RAPPORT.md) · Lathund: [`docs/GIT-LATHUND.md`](../../docs/GIT-LATHUND.md)

## Default

- Develop on **`main`**; push only **`origin`** (Livskompassen3.0). Never **`origin-old`**.
- Branch map: [`docs/BRANCH-KARTA.md`](../../docs/BRANCH-KARTA.md).

## When user approves work ("klart", "godkänt", "merge")

1. **Do NOT merge/delete yet.** Produce **Pre-Merge Impact Report (PMIR)** per `docs/MERGE-IMPACT-RAPPORT.md`.
2. **Wait** for explicit user OK ("godkänn merge", "kör stängning").
3. **Then help:** checkout main, pull --ff-only, merge/cherry-pick, smoke, push origin main.
4. **Close branch** only if PMIR said so and smoke PASS; update `docs/BRANCH-KARTA.md`.

## MUST NOT

- Final merge or `git push origin --delete` without PMIR + user OK.
- Delete **parked** `feat/*` without user OK.
- Wholesale-merge diverged `feat/*` inkorg.
- Change `firestore.rules` or Sacred paths without explicit user order.

## Proactive

- Warn if not on `main` for routine work.
- Keep evaluations in `docs/evaluations/`, not `.orkester/`.
